00:16:36.560 --> 00:16:38.840
So tell me about the history of Myanmar.

00:16:38.840 --> 00:16:41.280
You were born there, and your parents are still there,

00:16:41.280 --> 00:16:42.360
or they came to America?

00:16:42.360 --> 00:16:43.640
They came to America.

00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:44.160
OK.

00:16:44.160 --> 00:16:47.950
So Myanmar has been a closed country for many, many

00:16:47.950 --> 00:16:48.240
years,

00:16:48.240 --> 00:16:49.480
about 50 years.

00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:53.520
And then in 2013, it became a democratic country

00:16:53.520 --> 00:16:55.240
for a short period.

00:16:55.240 --> 00:16:59.120
And then in 2022, right after--

00:16:59.120 --> 00:17:02.080
at the tail end of COVID, there was a military coup.

00:17:02.080 --> 00:17:05.520
So now it is a closed country again, and there is a--

00:17:05.520 --> 00:17:06.640
And explain that word.

00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:09.950
I know, but our audience may not know what is an open

00:17:09.950 --> 00:17:10.480
country

00:17:10.480 --> 00:17:11.680
or a closed country.

00:17:11.680 --> 00:17:12.480
Yeah.

00:17:12.480 --> 00:17:18.160
Well, closed country is really where everything is just

00:17:18.160 --> 00:17:20.040
controlled very, very tightly, right?

00:17:20.040 --> 00:17:22.280
Because you can't really talk about God.

00:17:22.280 --> 00:17:24.920
And in fact, one of our teachers,

00:17:24.920 --> 00:17:27.920
who is in an internally displaced village--

00:17:27.920 --> 00:17:30.280
internally displaced village meaning

00:17:30.280 --> 00:17:33.160
we have, because Myanmar has so many wars and so many

00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:36.480
disasters, there are a lot of people who are displaced

00:17:36.480 --> 00:17:37.640
from their homes.

00:17:37.640 --> 00:17:40.520
And we have a school there, and of course, as an

00:17:40.520 --> 00:17:41.320
outreach.

00:17:41.320 --> 00:17:43.640
So there's a school and a home church.

00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:47.360
And she was just told this week that she can no longer

00:17:47.360 --> 00:17:48.240
meet,

00:17:48.240 --> 00:17:49.840
have a church service at her home.

00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:52.850
She can still teach kids, thank God, but she cannot

00:17:52.850 --> 00:17:53.320
meet.

00:17:53.320 --> 00:17:55.080
So there is just a lot of controlling.

00:17:55.080 --> 00:17:57.240
So no churches, no gospel.

00:17:57.240 --> 00:17:58.800
It's closed to the gospel.

00:17:58.800 --> 00:18:02.800
And if Christians or missionaries or even pastors

00:18:02.800 --> 00:18:05.400
try to spread the gospel, sometimes they

00:18:05.400 --> 00:18:06.920
are persecuted by the government.

00:18:06.920 --> 00:18:08.920
Yeah, absolutely, yes.

00:18:08.920 --> 00:18:10.080
Does your story have a--

00:18:10.080 --> 00:18:12.520
does your family have a story about that?

00:18:12.520 --> 00:18:15.840
My family, no, because my family actually is--

00:18:15.840 --> 00:18:17.440
my parents are Buddhist.

00:18:17.440 --> 00:18:20.760
My mom and dad are actually Buddhist nuns and monks.

00:18:20.760 --> 00:18:24.270
I actually got to know Christ in college here in

00:18:24.270 --> 00:18:25.200
Indiana.

00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:26.080
OK.

00:18:26.080 --> 00:18:28.440
So now you are leading this mission.

00:18:28.440 --> 00:18:30.840
Who is the founder of the mission?

00:18:30.840 --> 00:18:31.800
How did it start?

00:18:31.800 --> 00:18:34.760
Yes, the founder of mission is Joanna Jones.

00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:37.800
I was actually-- she is from southern Indiana.

00:18:37.800 --> 00:18:40.020
I was living in Bloomington, Indiana right after

00:18:40.020 --> 00:18:40.440
college

00:18:40.440 --> 00:18:43.520
and going to a church, sure was a Christian.

00:18:43.520 --> 00:18:47.800
And my connect group leader, a Bible study group leader,

00:18:47.800 --> 00:18:53.790
his growing up in his childhood, his Sunday school

00:18:53.790 --> 00:18:54.120
teacher

00:18:54.120 --> 00:18:55.200
was Joanna.

00:18:55.200 --> 00:18:57.720
So Joanna was visiting Myanmar.

00:18:57.720 --> 00:19:00.800
And she met this man named Josiah.

00:19:00.800 --> 00:19:02.360
And they just talked about--

00:19:02.360 --> 00:19:04.400
he talked to her about his passion.

00:19:04.400 --> 00:19:06.520
And he's been praying to have--

00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:09.800
to serve as an orphanage, in an orphanage.

00:19:09.800 --> 00:19:13.430
Little did she know, she said, yes, I'll help you one

00:19:13.430 --> 00:19:13.960
day.

00:19:13.960 --> 00:19:17.640
And on her way back, while she was in the air,

00:19:17.640 --> 00:19:20.250
a cyclone nargis hit where millions and millions of

00:19:20.250 --> 00:19:20.520
people

00:19:20.520 --> 00:19:21.160
were killed.

00:19:21.160 --> 00:19:21.920
Oh, no.

00:19:21.920 --> 00:19:26.960
So there was a desire to help.

00:19:26.960 --> 00:19:28.000
The need was born.

00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:29.920
And she touched the ground.

00:19:29.920 --> 00:19:31.880
And the reason how I got involved

00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:33.520
was we were praying for her because we

00:19:33.520 --> 00:19:36.040
didn't know where she was, whether she was in the air,

00:19:36.040 --> 00:19:37.680
whether she was still in Burma.

00:19:37.680 --> 00:19:39.160
So we were praying for her safety.

00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:43.760
And she came back and she talked about, well, now we

00:19:43.760 --> 00:19:45.560
have a need for an orphanage.

00:19:45.560 --> 00:19:50.840
So Josiah went to the region where it was hit the most,

00:19:50.840 --> 00:19:54.240
very much Buddhist country area.

00:19:54.240 --> 00:19:58.400
I'm seeing there's like 16 dots on the map.

00:19:58.400 --> 00:20:00.160
Does that mean there are 16 locations

00:20:00.160 --> 00:20:01.360
where the mission is active?

00:20:01.360 --> 00:20:02.440
Yes, absolutely.

00:20:02.440 --> 00:20:02.960
Wow.

00:20:02.960 --> 00:20:05.840
So it expanded quite big from that little plane

00:20:05.840 --> 00:20:08.200
trip and the terrible cyclone.

00:20:08.200 --> 00:20:09.520
Now it is everywhere in Burma.

00:20:09.520 --> 00:20:11.040
Everywhere in Burma, yes.

00:20:11.040 --> 00:20:14.400
So we have lots of preschool up here

00:20:14.400 --> 00:20:16.400
in a lot of the remote areas.

00:20:16.400 --> 00:20:20.400
Again, preschool is very much a new concept over there

00:20:20.400 --> 00:20:20.840
as well.

00:20:20.840 --> 00:20:23.400
A lot of the time, a mother has to stay home

00:20:23.400 --> 00:20:27.240
or a father or the kids would just be watched,

00:20:27.240 --> 00:20:29.080
