00:20:29.080 --> 00:20:31.440
So we saw that as an opportunity to reach out to the

00:20:31.440 --> 00:20:31.800
children

00:20:31.800 --> 00:20:33.400
while they were still young.

00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:33.880
Yeah.

00:20:33.880 --> 00:20:37.400
Now Myanmar is the name of the country.

00:20:37.400 --> 00:20:37.920
Yes.

00:20:37.920 --> 00:20:41.280
But Burma is like the language or the culture.

00:20:41.280 --> 00:20:42.560
They're Burmese people.

00:20:42.560 --> 00:20:43.200
Yes.

00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:46.720
So really Myanmar has always been

00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:49.440
the name in our own language.

00:20:49.440 --> 00:20:52.480
But of course, Burma, Burmese, is

00:20:52.480 --> 00:20:56.440
given name when we were colonized by United Kingdom

00:20:56.440 --> 00:20:58.120
because that was just the easier way.

00:20:58.120 --> 00:21:01.280
The British did that to America also, actually.

00:21:01.280 --> 00:21:04.280
And we finally had a revolution, threw them out,

00:21:04.280 --> 00:21:05.440
and now we're America.

00:21:05.440 --> 00:21:07.480
So now you're Myanmar, right?

00:21:07.480 --> 00:21:10.840
So it's kind of the similar story.

00:21:10.840 --> 00:21:13.880
I love the British, but they gave us a common language.

00:21:13.880 --> 00:21:15.600
Now we can speak.

00:21:15.600 --> 00:21:18.120
So God bless them.

00:21:18.120 --> 00:21:21.880
